Purshasing Manager – Arabic Speaking
Adecco
Dubai, UAE
Posted on: 3 May 2014
THE ROLE
Expand all
DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
•Manage mutually beneficial relationships with assigned suppliers
•Ensure a continuous supply of goods to restaurants
•Negotiate and execute contracts with suppliers for new and existing products
•Monitor supplier compliance with contracts and determine necessary actions on an as needed basis to enforce compliance
•First responder on all Supply Chain Issues.
•Collaborate with Inventory Management, Marketing, Research & Development and Quality •Assurance to ensure successful promotions, new suppliers roll-outs, and new product introductions
•Coordinate and Support product samples and results with Culinary Department
•Maintain knowledge of supplier capabilities in your assigned product categories
•Provide assistance and forecasting to Inventory Management on an as needed basis
•Provide set up and maintenance information for new vendors and new items to Accounting
REQUIREMENTS
QUALIFICATIONS:
•Proficiency with Microsoft Office environment including Word, Excel and PowerPoint
•Ability to analyze, negotiate and manage contracts across all categories as needed
•Must have excellent communication and organizational skills and possess strong attention to detail and follow through
•Have the ability to work independently and to plan and accomplish a variety of tasks
•Must be able to identify problems and develop solutions
•Requires 5-7 years of experience in restaurant purchasing, as well as a good understanding of Finance & Accounting
•Four-year college degree is required and a master’s degree is a plus
•Team player, strong work ethic, ability to handle stress and work in a fast-paced environment
ABOUT THE COMPANY
The Adecco Group is the world's leading provider of HR solutions. With more than 33,000 FTE employees and a network of 5,600 branches, in over 60 countries and territories around the world, we offer a wide variety of services, connecting close to 750,000 associates with well over 100,000 clients every day.
The services we offer fall into the broad categories of temporary staffing, permanent placement, career transition, talent development and workforce management solutions, as well as outsourcing and consulting.
The Adecco Group is based in Zurich-Glattbrugg, Switzerland and we are a Fortune Global 500 company listed on the SIX Swiss Exchange.
